This is the level of rigor the Architecture Review Board (ARB) expects. When presenting a Golden Topology and Enterprise Patterns to leadership, you must balance high-level strategic vision with boots-on-the-ground engineering realities.

Here is the comprehensive architectural breakdown, complete with the visual topologies and the ARB playbook for implementation.

---

### **Context Understanding & Key Assumptions**

* **M&A Connectivity:** Acquired entities will not be immediately migrated to our core systems. We will use a "Hub and Spoke" integration model (Cluster Linking) to securely stream their data into our ecosystem.
* **Tiered SLA Infrastructure:** Not all data is created equal. We operate a Tier 1 (Mission Critical, Active-Active) and Tier 2 (Analytical, Active-Passive) infrastructure to optimize costs and isolate blast radii.
* **Operational Maturity:** Application teams are expected to manage their own Consumer Group offsets and implement idempotency. The Platform team manages the Kafka brokers, Zookeeper/KRaft, and the centralized Schema Registry.

