### **2. Topic Placement Decision Matrix**

Developers consistently struggle with *where* to put their data. Use this decision tree to enforce infrastructure tiering and prevent Tier 1 from being overwhelmed by low-value telemetry.

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    Start([Developer Requests New Topic]) --> Q1{Is this for an<br/>Acquired Bank/External Entity?}
    
    Q1 -->|Yes| Edge[Deploy to Edge/Spoke Cluster]
    Edge --> ACL_Route[Route through Anti-Corruption Layer]
    ACL_Route --> Hub_Eval
    
    Q1 -->|No| Hub_Eval{What is the Business Impact<br/>if this topic goes down?}
    
    Hub_Eval -->|Severe Financial/Regulatory Loss<br/>Fedwire, RTP, Ledger| T1{Requires Multi-Region<br/>Failover (RTO < 1 min)?}
    
    T1 -->|Yes| Tier1[Provision in Tier 1 Active-Active]
    
    Hub_Eval -->|Delayed Reporting, UI Glitches<br/>Clickstream, Batches, Analytics| T2{Is payload > 1MB?}
    
    T1 -->|No| Tier2
    T2 -->|No| Tier2[Provision in Tier 2 Active-Passive]
    
    T2 -->|Yes| ClaimCheck[Mandate Claim Check Pattern<br/>Store in S3, Publish Pointer to Tier 2]

```

